# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES — TEMPLATE
#
# This is a SAMPLE file. It is safe to commit and shows which secrets the app
# needs. To actually run the app:
#
#   1. Make a copy of this file in the same folder and name the copy ".env.local"
#   2. Fill in the real values below
#   3. Save. Never share .env.local or commit it to git — it holds your secrets.
#      (.env.local is already ignored by git for you.)
#
# Anything starting with NEXT_PUBLIC_ is sent to the browser and is NOT secret.
# Everything else stays on the server and IS secret.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Supabase (your database + logins) ---
# Find these in your Supabase project: Settings → API.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-public-anon-key

# Secret server-only key for admin tasks (optional, add when needed).
# Never expose this to the browser.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-secret-service-role-key

# --- Anthropic Claude (the AI that does the estimating) ---
# Find this at https://console.anthropic.com → API Keys.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-secret-anthropic-key
